WebhookPayload.description:
The JSON body delivered to your webhook endpoint when a Docuplete form is submitted. Every delivery is signed — verify the `X-Docuplete-Signature` header before processing.

**Signature verification**

Each request includes:
```
X-Docuplete-Signature: sha256=<hex>
```
Verify by computing `HMAC-SHA256(webhookSecret, rawBody)` using your package's signing secret (available in the Docuplete dashboard under Webhooks → Signing secret).

**Node.js example**
```js
const crypto = require('crypto');
const sig = req.headers['x-docuplete-signature'];
const expected = 'sha256=' + crypto.createHmac('sha256', WEBHOOK_SECRET).update(rawBody).digest('hex');
if (!crypto.timingSafeEqual(Buffer.from(sig), Buffer.from(expected))) {
  return res.status(401).end('Invalid signature');
}
```
